quran[23]{c,v,t,f}:
  88,25,"Verily, to Us will be their return;"
  88,26,"Then verily, for Us will be their reckoning."
  89,22,"And your Lord comes with the angels in rows."
  89,23,"And Hell will be brought near that Day. On that Day will man remember, but how will that remembrance (then) avail him?"
  89,24,"He will say: "
  90,16,"Or to a Miskîn (poor) cleaving to dust (out of misery)."
  90,17,"Then he became one of those who believed (in the Islamic Monotheism) and recommended one another to perseverance and patience, and (also) recommended one another to pity and compassion."
  90,18,"They are those on the Right Hand (i.e. the dwellers of Paradise),"
  91,13,"But the Messenger of Allâh [Sâlih عليه السلام] said to them: "
  91,14,"Then they denied him and they killed it. So their Lord destroyed them because of their sin, and made them equal in destruction (i.e. all grades of people, rich and poor, strong and weak, etc.)!"
  91,15,"And He (Allâh) feared not the consequences thereof."
  92,10,"We will make smooth for him the path for evil."
  92,11,"And what will his wealth avail him when he goes down (in destruction)?."
  92,12,"Truly! On Us is (to give) guidance."
  93,7,"And He found you unaware (of the Qur’ân, its laws, and Prophethood) and guided you?"
  93,8,"And He found you poor and made you rich (self-sufficient with self-contentment)?"
  93,9,"Therefore, treat not the orphan with oppression."
  94,4,"And have We not raised high your fame?"
  94,5,"Verily, along with every hardship is relief,"
  94,6,"Verily, along with every hardship is relief (i.e. there is one hardship with two reliefs, so one hardship cannot overcome two reliefs)."
  95,1,"By the fig, and the olive."
  95,2,"By Mount Sinai."
  95,3,"By this city of security (Makkah).{1}",footnotes:1:(V.3) See footnote of (V.2:191).